Where do I start... the past few months I‚Äôve been lost. I‚Äôve been bouncing around couch to couch. Losing steam. Getting distracted. Allowing my current situation to get the best of me. I haven‚Äôt picked up a book, paintbrush, or weights in too long. I feel like I‚Äôve let my supporters down as well as my business and myself. I can‚Äôt express how much I appreciate my followers and those who have contributed to my business. I‚Äôve met marvelous people and formed fruitful relationships along the way. I had a fraudulent order back in early August that ended with my bank account closed with -$400 in it. @Shopify cut off my shop‚Äôs payment provisions which resulted in a few customers not being able to buy what they wanted. Without any online sales revenue, my @Shopify bill couldn‚Äôt be paid, resulting in not only my whole website being down, but my domain name being locked into @Shopify. My hands felt like they were tied but the truth is, they weren‚Äôt. I should have persisted and figured it out. With that being said, it is of no value to complain about what I should have done. All I‚Äôve got is today. Today I can make my vision a success story.
Thank you for reading- Shane
